  <section toc="hw" name="Hardware Emulators">
  <desc><p>This section describes emulators implemented in hardware</p>
<DL>
	<DT>The <a href="../upet/index.html">Micro-PET</a> and <A HREF="../ultipet/index.html">Ulti-PET</A></DT>
	<DD>
		The Micro- and Ulti-PET are complete PET re-builds on a single board. They use all modern components
		and can be built today without having to scavenge something from an old machine.
		They use FPGA as video generator, a 65816 CPU for more available memory, and can run
		up to 13.5 MHz, and have colour video, DAC audio, USB keyboard support.
		The Ulti-PET adds Dual-SID sound output, joystick ports (compatible with userport Joysticks from the
		original, Fast-IEC bus support, serial (RS232) interfaces, I2C, SPI interfaces, and even a proper expansion port.
		More detail on their <a href="https://github.com/fachat/upet_family">github page</a>.
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://dlehenbauer.github.io/econopet/40-8096-A.html">EconoPET</A></DT>
	<DD>
		The EconoPET allows to repair or upgrade a Commodore PET 2001-8096, but also provides an HDMI display and USB keyboard, so it 
		can be used as a standalone computer without PET case or keyboard.
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://github.com/Rhialto/MegaPET">MegaPET</A></DT>
	<DD>
		A PET core for the Mega65 FPGA retro machine (which started out as a C65 re-build but now runs a lot more different cores, 
		the PET being one of them).
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://github.com/skibo/Pet2001_Arty">Pet2001-Arty</A></DT>
	<DD>
		A recreation of the 2001 on a Xilinux Artix7 FPGA.
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://github.com/MiSTer-devel/PET2001_MiSTer">MiSTer PET2001 core</A></DT>
	<DD>
		A recreation of the 2001 on MiSTer machine, that allows to run a number of different retro machines, the PET being one of them.
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://www.tfw8b.com/product/minipet-40-80-standalone-computer-kit/">MiniPET 40/80</A></DT>
	<DD>
		A real PET re-build by Tynemouth software and sold by TFW8b.com (look at their page for kits and other variants)
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="https://commodorepetmini.com/">Commodore PET Mini</A></DT>
	<DD>
		This is a PET emulator running on a raspberry pi board, inside a mini PET-like case.
	</DD>

	<DT><A HREF="../csa/index.html">CS/A65</A></DT>
	<DD>The CS/A65 computer is not a software emulator, but a hardware emulator.
	It provides a very highly compatible system. In fact it runs a patched
	3032 ROM just fine. Only a few IEEE488 lines have been moved around,
	and the CRTC still needs to be set to 80 columns and not 40 to display
	80 columns.</DD>

	<DT>A Commodore PET in an FPGA - Dead project?</DT>
	<DD>This is an amazing emulation - it emulates the complete PET in an FPGA! 
	The emulation is based on a Diligent Nexys3 FPGA evaluation board, implemented in verilog with Xilinx' ISE 13.2. 
	Source code is available! The CPU is not cycle-exact, but it runs Space Invaders and other games just fine.
	Unfortunately, as of 2026, this project does not seem to be available anymore.
	</DD>
</DL>
